  {
    "id": "1779663129724.0",
    "schoolName": "Kingsbury High School",
    "userType": "parent",
    "rating": 4,
    "reviewText": "My son has been at Kingsbury High School for two years now, and overall we're very satisfied with our choice. When we were looking at schools, we were torn between Kingsbury High and another local school, but we're glad we chose Kingsbury.\n\nThe teaching quality is consistently high across most subjects. The maths and English departments are particularly strong, with teachers who go the extra mile to help students who are struggling. My son was finding science challenging, but his teacher arranged additional support sessions during lunch breaks, and his grades have improved significantly.\n\nFacilities are a mixed bag. The new building is fantastic - bright, modern, and well-equipped. The older parts of the school could do with some refurbishment. The sports facilities are adequate, though my son wishes there was a better indoor sports hall.\n\nCommunication from the school has improved over the past year. The introduction of a new parent app has made it easier to receive updates about homework and events. The headteacher's weekly newsletter is informative.\n\nThe school's pastoral care is excellent. When my son had a bereavement in the family, the school was incredibly supportive. The head of year knows every child by name and seems genuinely invested in their wellbeing.\n\nIn summary, Kingsbury High School is a solid choice. It provides a good education in a supportive environment. The strengths far outweigh the weaknesses, and my son is happy there. I would recommend this school to other parents.",
    "reviewTitle": "Happy and Safe Environment",
    "recommend": "yes",
    "yearFrom": "2022.0",
    "yearTo": "2026.0",
    "yearGroup": null,
