  {
    "id": "1779663129725.0",
    "schoolName": "Kingsbury High School",
    "userType": "parent",
    "rating": 4,
    "reviewText": "I wanted to share a comprehensive review of Kingsbury High School based on our family's experience over the past three years. When we first moved to the area, we were nervous about choosing the right school for our daughter, who was about to start Year 7. After visiting several schools, we felt that Kingsbury High had the warmest atmosphere and the most engaged staff.\n\nThe first thing I noticed was how welcoming the reception staff were when we arrived for our open evening. They remembered our names when we came back for a second visit, which really impressed me. The headteacher gave a presentation that was honest about the school's challenges as well as its strengths.\n\nAcademically, our daughter has made excellent progress. She started with below-average scores in maths but with the help of excellent teachers and after-school support, she is now working above expectations. The school's approach to homework is sensible - not overwhelming, but enough to reinforce learning.\n\nPastoral care is where this school truly shines. When our daughter was having friendship difficulties, her form tutor noticed something was wrong before we even mentioned it. She set up a meeting with us, arranged mediation sessions, and the issue was resolved within two weeks.\n\nThe facilities are generally good. The science labs were recently refurbished and are modern and well-equipped. The library is a particular highlight - well-stocked with excellent reading programs. My daughter has developed a love of reading thanks to her encouragement.\n\nExtracurricular opportunities are plentiful. Our daughter has tried netball, drama club, and coding club. The school choir performed at a local venue recently, which was wonderful.\n\nCommunication from the school is generally good, though sometimes emails from subject teachers can take a few days. The parent portal is useful, and the weekly newsletter keeps us informed about upcoming events.\n\nThe only area needing improvement is the school meals. The options are limited and could be healthier. The queues are too long during peak times. This seems to be a common issue among students.\n\nOverall, we are very happy with Kingsbury High School. Our daughter is thriving academically and socially, and she feels safe and supported. The staff genuinely care about the students, and the leadership team is visible and approachable. I would definitely recommend this school to other parents.",
    "reviewTitle": "Happy and Safe Environment",
    "recommend": "yes",
